OL,3,CSenior minister says charities may
OL,4,Cneed to merge to bring down costs
OL,6,F"I can think of a number of charities
OL,7,Fwho could bring down their operating
OL,8,Fcosts by sharing overhead costs and
OL,9,Fthat's an area I'm going to try and
OL,10,Fencourage in discussions with the
OL,11,Fcharities going forward."
OL,13,FMarcus Liddiard, Chair of the
OL,14,FAssociation of Jersey Charities, says:
OL,15,F"There is always the opportunity for
OL,16,Fchallenge and things to be done better.
OL,18,F"I think fundamentally charities are
OL,19,Falready incredibly lean. They only
OL,20,Fexist because of need.
