OL,3,CSenior minister says charities may
OL,4,Cneed to merge to bring down costs
OL,6,F"If fewer charities exist, the needs
OL,7,Fstill exist so who funds that gap?"
OL,9,F"If you look at how we operate today,
OL,10,Fthere are a lot of cancer charities
OL,11,Fbut they all support a specific niche,
OL,12,Fbe it supporting different types of
OL,13,Fpeople and different types of cancer.
OL,15,F"There is a big array of those that
OL,16,Fwork really well together. You can
OL,17,Flook at the homelessness charities,
OL,18,Fthere is a big cluster but they all
OL,19,Fhave their individual roles within
OL,20,Fthat."
